{{十干十二支}} '''Ren''' (壬) is the 9th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干}}.
== Overview == * The origin of the Chinese character "壬" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Reappearance of Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=110–11}}</ref> It is used as a borrowed character to denote the ninth of the Ten Heavenly Stems. * Years ending with the digit 2 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|西暦}} correspond to the {{ill|Ren|ja|壬}} year. Additionally, when representing the year, it is also known by the name '''Xuanyi''' (玄黓).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternate Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法}}, "Ren" is used in the names of compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基}} containing nine carbon atoms, such as {{ill|nonane|ja|ノナン}} and {{ill|nonyl group|ja|ノニル基}}. * The counterpart of Ren is {{ill|Ding|ja|丁}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方}} associated with Ren is north-northwest, slightly north (345 degrees).
[[Category:Chinese characters]] [[Category:Ten Heavenly Stems]] [[ja:壬]]
