{{十干十二支}}
'''Ren''' (壬) is the 9th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4d707a1e4dd930dc3b4490eea48871fc708a7245ce283f1e60d71f2dc1d03e10JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Mizunoe+(%e5%a3%ac)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjAxNyZlbGVtZW50X2lkPTcxOTU5&ntb=1</ref>

== Overview ==
* The origin of the Chinese character "壬" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Reappearance of Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=110–11}}</ref> It is used as a borrowed character to denote the ninth of the Ten Heavenly Stems.
* Years ending with the digit 2 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} correspond to the {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} year. Additionally, when representing the year, it is also known by the name '''Xuanyi''' (玄黓).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternate Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08}}</ref>
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, "Ren" is used in the names of compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} containing nine carbon atoms, such as {{ill|nonane|ja|ノナン|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|nonyl group|ja|ノニル基|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* The counterpart of Ren is {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} associated with Ren is north-northwest, slightly north (345 degrees).
