{{十干十二支|qq=}} '''Ren''' (壬) is the 9th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干|qq=|qq=draft}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4d707a1e4dd930dc3b4490eea48871fc708a7245ce283f1e60d71f2dc1d03e10JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Mizunoe+(%e5%a3%ac)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjAxNyZlbGVtZW50X2lkPTcxOTU5&ntb=1</ref>
== Overview == * The origin of the Chinese character "壬" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Reappearance of Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=110–11|qq=}}</ref> It is used as a borrowed character to denote the ninth of the Ten Heavenly Stems. * Years ending with the digit 2 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=|qq=draft}} correspond to the {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|qq=|qq=draft}} year. Additionally, when representing the year, it is also known by the name '''Xuanyi''' (玄黓).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternate Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=|qq=draft}}, "Ren" is used in the names of compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基|qq=|qq=draft}} containing nine carbon atoms, such as {{ill|nonane|ja|ノナン|qq=|qq=draft}} and {{ill|nonyl group|ja|ノニル基|qq=|qq=draft}}. * The counterpart of Ren is {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=|qq=draft}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|qq=draft}} associated with Ren is north-northwest, slightly north (345 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Mizunoe (壬)==
{| class="wikitable alternance droite" |{{ill|Yang Water Monkey|ja|壬申|zh|壬申|ko|임신|fr|Singe d'eau|de|Wasser-Affe|en|Water Monkey|lt=壬申 (Yang Water Monkey)|lt_ko=임신|qq=|qq=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Water Horse|ja|壬午|zh|壬午|ko|임오|fr|Cheval d'eau|de|Wasser-Pferd|en|Water Horse|lt=壬午 (Yang Water Horse)|lt_ko=임오|qq=|qq=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Water Dragon|ja|壬辰|zh|壬辰|ko|임진|fr|Dragon d'eau|de|Wasser-Drache|en|Water Dragon|lt=壬辰 (Yang Water Dragon)|lt_ko=임진|qq=|qq=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Water Tiger|ja|壬寅|zh|壬寅|ko|임인|fr|Tigre d'eau|de|Wasser-Tiger|en|Water Tiger|lt=壬寅 (Yang Water Tiger)|lt_ko=임인|qq=|qq=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Water Rat|ja|壬子|zh|壬子|ko|임자|fr|Rat d'eau|de|Wasser-Ratte|en|Water Rat|lt=壬子 (Yang Water Rat)|lt_ko=임자|qq=|qq=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Water Dog|ja|壬戌|zh|壬戌|ko|임술|fr|Chien d'eau|de|Wasser-Hund|en|Water Dog|lt=壬戌 (Yang Water Dog)|lt_ko=임술|qq=|qq=draft}} |}
