== Pronunciations: 壬 (Stem 9) == * Chinese (Pinyin): Rén * Korean: Im (임) * Vietnamese: Nhâm * Japanese: ** On’yomi: Jin (じん) ** Kunyomi (elemental): Mizunoe (みずのえ, 水の兄 – “Elder Water”)
== Overview == * The origin of the Chinese character "壬" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Reappearance of Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=110–11|qq=}}</ref> It is used as a borrowed character to denote the ninth of the Ten Heavenly Stems. * Years ending with the digit 2 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] correspond to the {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|lt=Mizunoe (壬)|2=ja|3=壬|4=zh|5=壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ren|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoe (壬)|qq=}} year. Additionally, when representing the year, it is also known by the name '''Xuanyi''' (玄黓).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternate Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=}}, "Ren" is used in the names of compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/functional groups|qq=}} containing nine carbon atoms, such as [[:en:Nonane|nonane]] and {{ill|nonyl group|ja|ノニル基|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/nonyl group|qq=}}. * The counterpart of Ren is {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|lt=Hinoto (丁)|2=ja|3=丁|4=zh|5=丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ding|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoto (丁)|qq=}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} associated with Ren is north-northwest, slightly north (345 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Mizunoe (壬)==
