{{Ten Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches}}
'''Mizunoe''' (壬) is the 9th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|en|Heavenly Stems|qid=Q1190985|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|1=Heavenly Stems}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4d707a1e4dd930dc3b4490eea48871fc708a7245ce283f1e60d71f2dc1d03e10JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Mizunoe+(%e5%a3%ac)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjAxNyZlbGVtZW50X2lkPTcxOTU5&ntb=1</ref>

== Pronunciations: 壬 (Stem 9) ==
* Chinese (Pinyin): Rén  
* Korean: Im (임)  
* Vietnamese: Nhâm  
* Japanese:  
** On’yomi: Jin (じん)  
** Kunyomi (elemental): Mizunoe (みずのえ, 水の兄 – “Elder Water”)

== Overview ==
* The origin of the Chinese character "壬" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Reappearance of Chinese Characters: From Old Knowledge to New Insights| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=110–11|qq=}}</ref> It is used as a borrowed character to denote the ninth of the Ten Heavenly Stems.
* Years ending with the digit 2 in the {{ill|Common Era|en|Common Era|qid=Q208141|lt=Common Era|1=Common Era}} correspond to the {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|lt=Mizunoe (壬)|2=ja|3=壬|4=zh|5=壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ren|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoe (壬)|qq=}} year. Additionally, when representing the year, it is also known by the name '''Xuanyi''' (玄黓).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternate Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref>
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to IUPAC命名法|1=IUPAC nomenclature of chemistry|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q20826683}}, "Ren" is used in the names of compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/functional groups|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 基|1=Functional group|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q170409}} containing nine carbon atoms, such as {{ill|Nonane|en|Nonane|qid=Q150694|lt=nonane|1=Nonane}} and {{ill|nonyl group|ja|ノニル基|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/nonyl group|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
* The counterpart of Ren is {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|lt=Hinoto (丁)|2=ja|3=丁|4=zh|5=丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ding|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoto (丁)|qq=}}.
* The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 歳徳神}} associated with Ren is north-northwest, slightly north (345 degrees).
